</P>
<P>
   KHARTOUM, Sudan (AP) -- Sudan's Central Bank today ordered most
of the nation's two dozen banks to reorganize into six groups to
improve their financial strength and allow them to compete better
internationally. Under the plan, the majority of the banks,
including two public sector banks, would be grouped into financial
institutions with a minimum capital of 30 billion Sudanese pounds
($1.2 billion). The new guidelines do not apply to specialized
banks and branches of foreign banks, which are mainly subsidiaries
of Arab banks.
</P>
