<HEADLINE> Celebrity Spotlight &AMP; Birthdays  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   
<TEXT>
<P>
   In the birthday spotlight:
</P>
<P>
   Stephen Baldwin stars as Barney Rubble in the new film ''The
Flintstones in Viva Rock Vegas.'' Baldwin, who was born on May 12,
1966, is the youngest of the four acting Baldwin brothers. His
previous films include ''Last Exit to Brooklyn,'' ''The Usual
Suspects'' and ''Friends and Lovers.'' He will appear in the
upcoming film ''Cutaway'' with Tom Berenger.
</P>
<P>
   Gabriel Byrne, Cherry Jones and Roy Dotrice star in the revival
of Eugene O'Neill's ''A Moon for the Misbegotten'' at the Walter
Kerr Theater on Broadway. Byrne played the part of Satan in the
Arnold Schwarzenegger film ''End of Days.'' His other films include
''The Man in the Iron Mask,'' ''Polish Wedding'' and ''Stigmata.''
Byrne was born on May 12, 1950.
</P>
<P>
   George Carlin began performing comic routines in nightclubs in
the 1960s. ''Then I changed from being a superficial comic and
began to entertain people who would be considered counterculture:
college kids and hippies. I had a rebellious side of me that needed
expression,'' he says. Carlin played the part of Cardinal Glick in
Kevin Smith's film ''Dogma.'' His 1997 book ''Brain Droppings,''
published by Hyperion, was a best seller. Carlin was born on May
12, 1937.
</P>
<P>
   Celebrity birthdays May 7-13:
</P>
<P>
   May 7: ''Meet the Press'' host Tim Russert is 50. Actor Robert
Hegyes (''Welcome Back, Kotter'') is 49. Musician Phil Campbell of
Motorhead is 39. Singer-musician Chris O'Connor of Primitive Radio
Gods is 35. Actress Traci Lords is 31.
</P>
<P>
   May 8: Comedian Don Rickles is 74. Singer Toni Tennille is 57.
Musician Alex Van Halen of Van Halen is 45. Actress Melissa Gilbert
is 36. Musician Dave Rowntree of Blur is 36. Singer Enrique
Iglesias is 25. Actress Julia Whelan (''Once and Again'') is 15.
</P>
<P>
   May 9: CBS News correspondent Mike Wallace is 82. Actor Albert
Finney (''Erin Brockovich'') is 64. Actress Glenda Jackson is 64.
Singer Tommy Roe is 58. Actress Candice Bergen is 54. Singer Billy
Joel is 51. Singer David Gahan of Depeche Mode is 38. Rapper
Ghostface Killah is 30. Singer Tamia is 25. Musician Dan Regan of
Reel Big Fish is 23.
</P>
<P>
   May 10: Singer Donovan is 54. Singer Bono of U2 is 40. Rapper
Young MC is 33. Actor Erik Palladino (''ER'') is 32. Singer Jason
Dalyrimple of Soul for Real is 20.
</P>
<P>
   May 11: Comedian Mort Sahl is 73. Actress Natasha Richardson is
37. Actor Austin O'Brien (''Promised Land'') is 20.
</P>
<P>
   May 12: Actress Katharine Hepburn is 93. Composer Burt Bacharach
is 71. Comedian George Carlin is 63. Singer Steve Winwood is 52.
Actress Lindsay Crouse (''The Insider'') is 52. Actor Gabriel Byrne
is 50. Country singer Kix Brooks of Brooks and Dunn is 45. Actor
Ving Rhames is 39. Actor Emilio Estevez is 38. Actor Stephen
Baldwin is 34. Actress Jamie Luner (''Profiler'') is 29. Singer
Melanie Chisholm (Mel C./Sporty Spice) of Spice Girls is 24. Actor
Jason Biggs (''American Pie'') is 22. Actors Sullivan and Sawyer
Sweeten (''Everybody Loves Raymond'') are 5.
