<HEADLINE> 2 Ferries Sink in Bangladesh River  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) -- Two ferries caught in a storm sank in
the Meghna River in eastern Bangladesh, killing at least 73 people
and leaving more than 100 missing and feared drowned, officials
said.
</P>
<P>
   On Wednesday, a day after the accidents, rescuers pulled out 27
more bodies from the passenger cabins of the two ferries. A search
for those still missing was suspended at nightfall.
</P>
<P>
   The MV Dolphin capsized Tuesday with over 150 people aboard 50
miles east of Dhaka, the Bangladeshi capital. In neighboring
Narsingdi district, at least 20 passengers swam ashore as their
ferry, Bengal Bird, began sinking with 61 people aboard.
</P>
<P>
   Officials said it was unlikely any more survivors would be
found.
</P>
