<HEADLINE> Dow Down 300; Nasdaq Almost 200  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average plunged more
than 300 points today as interest-rate worries weighed on the
market and investors punished companies that warned of slowing
earnings growth. Weakness in blue-chip stocks spread to the broader
market, sending the Nasdaq composite down nearly 200 points.
</P>
<P>
   With an hour remaining in Wall Street's regular session, the Dow
Jones industrial average was down 313.97 to 10,417.15. The Dow's
declines were broad-based, with AT&AMP;T, Hewlett-Packard and Wal-Mart
all stumbling.
</P>
<P>
   Broader stock indicators were also sharply lower. The Nasdaq
composite index was down 186.11 to 3,599.34 and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 index was down 40.23 to 1,406.04.
</P>
<P>
   Stocks fell for a second session as interest-rate fears kept
many buyers on the sidelines. The Federal Reserve is widely
