<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Clear skies stretched from the Northeast to the
Southeast on
Wednesday, while thunderstorms rolled through the Mississippi
Valley.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Showers and thunderstorms moved through sections of Tennessee,
southern Missouri, Arkansas, eastern Texas and Louisiana. Some were
heavy, with Lake Charles, La., recording more than 4 inches of
rainfall.
</P>
<P>
   Mostly clear skies and dry conditions dominated from the
Northeast and Great Lakes down to the Southeast.
</P>
<P>
   A weak cold front pushed east through the northern Plains and
central Rocky Mountains. A few showers were possible in northern
Wisconsin and Minnesota.
</P>
<P>
   A more active system moved into the Northwest, bringing showers
to Idaho, Washington and Oregon. The Southwest was mostly warm and
dry.
</P>
<P>
   Temperatures across the Lower 48 ranged from a low of 23 degrees
in Berlin, N.H., and Houlton, Maine, to an early-afternoon high of
88 in Yuma, Ariz.
</P>
