<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that are moving substantially or trading
heavily today on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock
Market.
</P>
<P>
NYSE
</P>
<P>
Bestfoods, up 10 7/8 at 61 7/16
Unilever NV, down 2 3/16 at 22 9/16
</P>
<P>
   Bestfoods, the maker of such household food products as Skippy
peanut butter and Hellmann's mayonnaise, rejected an $18.4 billion
takeover offer from multinational consumer products conglomerate
Unilever, saying the $66-a-share offer was not financially adequate
and not in the best interest of shareholders.
</P>
<P>
Wal-Mart Stores Inc., down 4 1/4 at 53 3/8
Kohl's Corp., down 3 13/16 at 48
</P>
<P>
   Goldman Sachs downgraded a number of retail companies from its
recommended list, but still labeled them ''market outperform.''
Goldman said current growth rates are unsustainable for the second
half of the year.
</P>
<P>
Martha Stewart Living Omnimedia Inc., up 4 at 20
</P>
<P>
   The publishing and merchandising company posted first-quarter
profits of 11 cents per share, coasting past analysts' estimates of
4 cents per share. Martha Stewart cited strong revenue growth in
the electronic commerce and publishing divisions.
</P>
<P>
NASDAQ
</P>
<P>
Novell Inc., down 6 15/16 at 10 5/8
</P>
<P>
   The company said second-quarter earnings will be sharply lower
than expected after the February introduction of Microsoft's
Windows 2000 froze sales of its competing operating system.
</P>
<P>
S1 Corp., down 17 1/16 at 42 5/16
</P>
<P>
   The company's first-quarter losses widened to $1.49 per share
from 13 cents per share in last year's first quarter. S1, a
developer of electronic-commerce Internet applications, cited
merger-related costs and stock option compensation expenses.
</P>
<P>
Wet Seal Inc., down 3\ at 15
</P>
<P>
   The clothing retailer expects to post first quarter earnings of
16 cents to 18 cents per share, down from earnings of 34 cents a
share in the year-ago period. Wet Seal said sales at stores open at
least a year fell 4.7 percent during the quarter.
</P>
<P>
Pharmacopeia Inc., down 14 9/16 at 28
</P>
<P>
   The company's first-quarter losses widened to 27 cents per
share, from 3 cents per share in the first quarter of 1999.
Pharmacopeia, a developer of drug discovery programs based on
small-molecule chemistry, said the first quarter is typically slow.
</P>
