<HEADLINE> Mich. Mom Shot Two Children, Self  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SYLVAN TOWNSHIP, Mich. (AP) -- Autopsies showed a woman found
dead in her home with two of her children shot the youths before
killing herself, an investigator said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   ''We have no other evidence that indicates any other scenario,''
Michigan State Police Lt. Beth Moranty said. ''Why she would do
that I don't think we're ever going to know.''
</P>
<P>
   Janice Young's husband, Daniel Young, and other relatives have
been cooperative with investigators but unable to pinpoint why the
38-year-old woman would kill Cooper Young, 9, and Makenzie Young,
4, before taking her own life, Moranty said.
</P>
<P>
   Moranty said autopsies revealed that Makenzie was shot once in
the head, Cooper once in the chest before their mother apparently
killed herself with a single shot to the head. They were found
Tuesday morning.
</P>
<P>
   Another child, Sydney Young, 12, was grazed on the head by a
bullet but was not seriously injured.
</P>
<P>
   ''Our family is deeply saddened by yesterday's events,'' Daniel
Young and family said in a written statement. ''We want everyone to
know that we have been a very loving family, and an extremely close
one, and that we love our children very much.''
</P>
</TEXT>
