<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 'Survivor' Contestant Arraigned  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEWPORT, R.I. (AP) -- A contestant on the reality CBS TV show
''Survivor'' pleaded innocent Wednesday to allegations he abused
his 9-year-old son.
</P>
<P>
   Richard Hatch, 39, was arraigned in Family Court on a charge of
second-degree child abuse.
</P>
<P>
   The boy told police that Hatch, just back from being marooned on
a remote tropical island off Borneo for the television program,
woke him at 4:30 a.m. one morning to go running because he wanted
the boy to lose weight.
</P>
<P>
   The boy said when he got tired and started walking, Hatch pulled
him by the ear and wrapped his hands around his neck to move him
along.
</P>
<P>
   Hatch's lawyer, Christopher Behan, did not return calls to his
office. Hatch's friends have said the boy, who Hatch adopted, was
troubled and lied about the incident.
</P>
<P>
   Hatch was among a group of 16 people left on the remote island
in March to live without running water or electricity. Every three
nights, the contestants voted to eject someone from the community.
It was not revealed how long Hatch lasted.
</P>
<P>
   The final person left at the end will get $1 million.
</P>
<P>
   CBS has said the show will go forward with Hatch in it. The show
will be aired weekly starting May 31.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
