   COLORADO: LHP Brian Bohanon reluctantly accepted a demotion to
the bullpen. ''I didn't sign here to be a reliever,'' said Bohanon,
who is in the second year of a three-year, $9 million contract. ''I
signed here to be a starter. Come on. You didn't expect me to be
happy, did you?'' Bohanon, who is 0-3 with a 9.67 ERA. ... RHP
Jerry Dipoto had surgery to repair a bulging disk below his neck
and will miss the rest of the season. ... C Scott Servais, who
missed 14 games with a sprained right ankle, was activated from the
DL and went 2-for-5 in his first game since April 17. He was
injured while stepping on a ball during batting practice and his
teammates welcomed him back with a sign on the batting cage that
said: ''DANGER. Watch your step!'' The sign also had a sketch of a
foot stepping on a ball. ... Colorado set a club record by scoring
16 runs without a homer. The previous high was 14 runs April 16
against St. Louis. ... OF Tom Goodwin left the game in the fifth
inning with a strained left adductor muscle. His status is
