<HEADLINE> Crew 2, United 1  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Richie Williams' own goal in the 88th minute
gave Columbus a 2-1 victory over D.C. United on Wednesday night,
the Crew's first ever victory in Washington.
</P>
<P>
   Williams accidentally headed the ball past goalkeeper Mark
Simpson after a throw-in.
</P>
<P>
   Columbus, which lost its first 13 matches in Washington,
improved to 3-4-1. United dropped to 1-5-1.
</P>
<P>
   The Crew opened the scoring in the 52nd minute when Robert
Warzycha sent a direct free kick around the United wall. The free
kick was awarded when Dante Washington was taken down just outside
the penalty area by defender Carey Talley.
</P>
<P>
   Talley tied it in the 57th minute on a header off Jaime Moreno's
crossing pass.
</P>
