<HEADLINE> Nearly 6 Tons of Marijuana Found  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   EL PASO, Texas (AP) -- U.S. Customs Service inspectors stopped a
tractor-trailer loaded with nearly 6 tons of marijuana as the
driver tried to enter the country, the agency said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   The driver fled on foot back to Mexico.
</P>
<P>
   Gene Kerven, El Paso port director for the Customs Service, said
Tuesday's seizure was the largest in the region in more than a
decade. The drugs have an estimated street value of $11.5 million.
</P>
<P>
   A drug-sniffing dog on the Zaragosa International Bridge on El
Paso's southeast side alerted inspectors to the truck. Two
inspectors then discovered a total of 11,541 pounds of marijuana in
80 cardboard boxes that were mixed in with boxes of car seat belts,
Kerven said.
</P>
</TEXT>
